WEBVTT

﻿1
00:04:11.767 --> 00:04:13.352
I'll kill them!

2
00:04:13.811 --> 00:04:15.354
I'll kill them all!

3
00:04:15.688 --> 00:04:17.815
Traitors and villains!

4
00:04:17.899 --> 00:04:19.525
- They dare strike at me!
- Your Grace.

5
00:04:19.609 --> 00:04:22.236
- I am the king!
- Your Grace! Yes. yes.

6
00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:24.780
- I am the king!
- Your Grace. Please. Your Grace.

7
00:04:26.115 --> 00:04:27.700
Traitors and villains!

8
00:04:29.577 --> 00:04:31.037
Fire from the sky.

9
00:04:31.245 --> 00:04:34.207
This is war! I declare war!

10
00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:37.251
I declare war!

11
00:05:34.017 --> 00:05:35.685
The gates have been shut.

12
00:05:37.520 --> 00:05:39.147
The search progresses.

13
00:05:40.482 --> 00:05:42.192
The villain will be found.

14
00:05:43.943 --> 00:05:46.362
We mustn't be shaken by this.

15
00:05:50.492 --> 00:05:51.910
This act.

16
00:05:55.914 --> 00:05:58.374
- The child.
- The child is dead.

17
00:06:01.836 --> 00:06:03.338
His pain is ended.

18
00:06:07.175 --> 00:06:09.886
But what they've done to...
to my girl...

19
00:06:10.428 --> 00:06:11.721
Yes.

20
00:06:25.986 --> 00:06:28.363
And they will pay for this.

21
00:06:39.583 --> 00:06:40.625
Who will pay?

22
00:06:40.709 --> 00:06:43.795
Whosever hand did this
or caused it to be done.

23
00:06:43.879 --> 00:06:47.799
And what if the hand that's done it
is not who must be blamed?

24
00:06:49.759 --> 00:06:51.219
The gods punish us.

25
00:06:51.553 --> 00:06:53.013
They punish me.

26
00:06:54.681 --> 00:06:56.141
For what sin?

27
00:07:00.395 --> 00:07:01.813
Daughter. listen to me.

28
00:07:02.063 --> 00:07:03.940
We will mourn as we must

29
00:07:04.024 --> 00:07:08.779
but some good may yet come of this.

30
00:07:11.364 --> 00:07:13.075
And where were
the members of this council

31
00:07:13.158 --> 00:07:14.743
while the murderer
threatened their king?

32
00:07:14.826 --> 00:07:16.036
Were you also threatened. Your Grace?

33
00:07:16.119 --> 00:07:17.371
I could have been!

34
00:07:21.333 --> 00:07:24.044
My son is my legacy!

35
00:07:25.170 --> 00:07:28.090
My son is heir to the Iron Throne!

36
00:07:29.841 --> 00:07:33.303
And where were you.
the Lord Commander of my Kingsguard?

37
00:07:33.387 --> 00:07:35.847
I was abed. Your Grace.
having ordered the Night's Watch.

38
00:07:36.807 --> 00:07:38.016
Abed.

39
00:07:38.558 --> 00:07:39.893
Abed!

40
00:07:40.811 --> 00:07:43.772
Instead of safeguarding
the sanctity of my family!

41
00:07:44.189 --> 00:07:47.401
This is not the time for blind
accusations. Your Grace.

42
00:07:47.484 --> 00:07:49.027
We'll know who did this soon enough.

43
00:07:49.111 --> 00:07:51.572
Who did this? Who... what?

44
00:07:51.655 --> 00:07:53.949
Is there any question who did this?

45
00:07:54.074 --> 00:07:57.452
Who would do this
save the bitch queen of bastards

46
00:07:57.578 --> 00:08:00.164
the smug cunt of Dragonstone?

47
00:08:00.247 --> 00:08:03.417
There she sits across the bay.
on her rock. laughing at me.

48
00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:06.211
She's fucking laughing at me!

49
00:08:14.720 --> 00:08:16.430
You wished her life to be spared.

50
00:08:16.513 --> 00:08:17.723
If I may. Your Grace.

51
00:08:18.098 --> 00:08:19.266
My lords.

52
00:08:19.349 --> 00:08:21.143
The guard has detained someone.

53
00:08:21.852 --> 00:08:24.188
The man we apprehended
is known to us.

54
00:08:25.314 --> 00:08:26.607
He's a gold cloak.

55
00:08:27.441 --> 00:08:29.109
Noted for his brutal nature.

56
00:08:29.193 --> 00:08:31.653
We caught him.
fleeing the Gate of the Gods

57
00:08:31.779 --> 00:08:34.114
with the child's head in a sack.

58
00:08:36.617 --> 00:08:37.660
I'll kill him myself.

59
00:08:37.743 --> 00:08:41.246
We'd do well to get what information
we can from the blackguard.

60
00:08:43.165 --> 00:08:45.709
I trust in the mastery of your trade.
Lord Larys.

61
00:08:45.793 --> 00:08:48.254
Oh. always studying. always protocol.

62
00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:49.755
We know our enemy!

63
00:08:49.838 --> 00:08:52.716
A king may have more than
one enemy. Your Grace.

64
00:08:53.384 --> 00:08:56.387
We would do well to ascertain
if this is your sister's hand

65
00:08:57.012 --> 00:09:00.307
or if there is a serpent
nestled closer to our bosoms.

66
00:09:00.391 --> 00:09:02.268
I suppose you're right. Ironrod.

67
00:09:03.394 --> 00:09:04.937
Could be anyone.

68
00:09:06.230 --> 00:09:09.108
It could be any one of you
in this room.

69
00:09:19.493 --> 00:09:21.370
Lord Jasper is correct.

70
00:09:22.204 --> 00:09:24.373
In one sense.
we must determine what happened

71
00:09:24.457 --> 00:09:27.376
and if we in the Keep
are still in peril.

72
00:09:27.460 --> 00:09:29.211
In another sense. of course...

73
00:09:32.214 --> 00:09:33.591
it doesn't matter.

74
00:09:36.969 --> 00:09:38.596
You mean to blame Rhaenyra.

75
00:09:39.555 --> 00:09:41.640
Tell the realm she has done this.

76
00:09:41.724 --> 00:09:43.100
I'll have the realm told nothing.

77
00:09:43.184 --> 00:09:45.353
We were assaulted
within our own walls.

78
00:09:45.436 --> 00:09:48.773
Within our own beds.
I will not be seen as weak.

79
00:09:48.856 --> 00:09:51.651
You're already seen as weak. Aegon.

80
00:09:52.735 --> 00:09:54.236
You fucking...

81
00:10:00.743 --> 00:10:03.412
A hasty coronation.
a dragon escaping the pit.

82
00:10:03.496 --> 00:10:05.039
The people see an omen.

83
00:10:05.790 --> 00:10:07.166
They whisper in the streets.

84
00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:09.919
They say. perhaps Rhaenyra
should be queen.

85
00:10:10.086 --> 00:10:14.423
And so. you would name her.
"Monster. Slayer of infants."

86
00:10:15.341 --> 00:10:17.051
I would do more than that.

87
00:10:17.969 --> 00:10:20.972
A funeral progress.
Let them see the child.

88
00:10:21.055 --> 00:10:25.309
Let them look upon the works of
this pretender to the throne.

89
00:10:27.687 --> 00:10:28.980
Father.

90
00:10:31.858 --> 00:10:33.860
- My king?
- No.

91
00:10:34.652 --> 00:10:38.030
I will not have my little son's body

92
00:10:38.197 --> 00:10:39.907
dragged through the street
like a dead dog.

93
00:10:39.991 --> 00:10:41.743
Not dragged! Honored!

94
00:10:42.744 --> 00:10:46.914
Escorted to the dragon pit
to be burned as a Targaryen prince.

95
00:10:47.999 --> 00:10:49.292
Your Grace.

96
00:10:49.417 --> 00:10:50.710
No.

97
00:10:57.216 --> 00:10:59.677
Let no one say I do not grieve.

98
00:11:00.470 --> 00:11:02.930
Jaehaerys was my grandson.
I loved him.

99
00:11:03.014 --> 00:11:05.683
I will not have him die in vain.

100
00:11:06.768 --> 00:11:08.519
Those who declared for Rhaenyra

101
00:11:08.603 --> 00:11:11.105
will they still support her
when they hear of her depravity?

102
00:11:11.189 --> 00:11:13.232
Or will they rather not renounce her?

103
00:11:15.485 --> 00:11:19.405
Jaehaerys will do more for us now
than a thousand knights in battle.

104
00:11:25.954 --> 00:11:27.956
You will have your war. Your Grace.

105
00:11:28.039 --> 00:11:32.836
But if you wait a short time.
you may yet double your strength.

106
00:11:35.171 --> 00:11:36.464
Mother.

107
00:11:41.803 --> 00:11:44.931
The Hand sets on a difficult path.
my darling

108
00:11:45.014 --> 00:11:46.933
but it might be the right one.

109
00:11:47.976 --> 00:11:51.688
Let the Silent Sisters ready
the prince for his final journey.

110
00:11:52.063 --> 00:11:55.275
And riding behind him.
his mother the Queen

111
00:11:55.358 --> 00:11:57.360
and with her. the Queen Dowager.

112
00:11:57.444 --> 00:11:59.028
No. I do not wish to be a spectacle.

113
00:11:59.112 --> 00:12:02.407
The realm must see
the sorrow of the crown

114
00:12:02.782 --> 00:12:06.077
a sorrow best expressed
through its most gentle souls.

115
00:12:09.539 --> 00:12:14.252
I think you'll all agree
the king himself must be spared.

116
00:12:29.893 --> 00:12:32.062
There's to be a funeral
for Jaehaerys.

117
00:12:37.901 --> 00:12:40.487
We've been asked to ride on a wagon
behind his body.

118
00:12:46.409 --> 00:12:47.911
I don't want to.

119
00:12:49.496 --> 00:12:50.831
Neither do I.

120
00:12:53.291 --> 00:12:54.876
But when a thing like this happens

121
00:12:56.545 --> 00:12:58.630
a blow to the king
is a blow to the realm.

122
00:13:00.257 --> 00:13:02.426
When the people share our grief.
they draw closer to us.

123
00:13:02.509 --> 00:13:04.302
I don't want them closer.

124
00:13:05.095 --> 00:13:06.471
I don't know them.

125
00:13:07.973 --> 00:13:09.516
Sometimes. we have to pretend.

126
00:13:12.227 --> 00:13:13.520
Why?

127
00:13:14.312 --> 00:13:16.857
We are representatives of the throne.
We have a duty.

128
00:13:19.901 --> 00:13:22.821
Helaena. what you saw last night
when you came to my room...

129
00:13:22.904 --> 00:13:24.489
This is for my boy.

130
00:14:43.694 --> 00:14:46.530
I was hired by Daemon Targaryen.

131
00:14:47.156 --> 00:14:50.159
He paid us. Half now.
half when the job is done.

132
00:14:50.242 --> 00:14:52.745
- Who is "us"?
- A... a ratcatcher.

133
00:14:53.537 --> 00:14:57.583
Employed by the household.
I don't know his right name.

134
00:15:06.467 --> 00:15:13.015
Behold the works of
Rhaenyra Targaryen!

135
00:15:15.434 --> 00:15:19.480
Pretender to the throne!

136
00:15:22.775 --> 00:15:24.568
Kingslayer!

137
00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:26.654
Deepest sympathies. my Queen.

138
00:15:26.737 --> 00:15:28.614
Gods be with you. my Queen.

139
00:15:28.697 --> 00:15:30.199
We support you. Queen Helaena.

140
00:15:30.282 --> 00:15:34.286
Defiler of the innocent!

141
00:15:41.752 --> 00:15:47.091
Behold the works of
Rhaenyra the cruel!

142
00:15:50.094 --> 00:15:51.470
Are you gonna hurt me?

143
00:15:52.805 --> 00:15:54.098
No.

144
00:15:55.766 --> 00:15:58.102
But I cannot vouch for His Grace.

145
00:16:23.002 --> 00:16:28.841
Behold the works
of Rhaenyra Targaryen!

146
00:16:28.925 --> 00:16:30.259
Our Queen!

147
00:16:30.927 --> 00:16:34.931
Pretender to the throne!

148
00:16:37.767 --> 00:16:39.602
Kingslayer!

149
00:16:41.270 --> 00:16:44.857
Defiler of the innocent!

150
00:16:59.539 --> 00:17:01.374
Queen Helaena!

151
00:17:06.921 --> 00:17:08.339
What's happening there?

152
00:17:09.674 --> 00:17:12.885
- Queen Helaena!
- What's going on? Move it. then!

153
00:17:18.141 --> 00:17:20.351
- Queen Helaena!
- Queen Helaena!

154
00:17:20.435 --> 00:17:21.936
Queen Helaena!

155
00:17:27.108 --> 00:17:28.651
Queen Helaena!

156
00:17:31.404 --> 00:17:32.489
Queen Helaena!

157
00:17:32.614 --> 00:17:34.032
- Helaena.
- Queen Helaena!

158
00:17:34.115 --> 00:17:36.951
- Heave! Heave!
- Queen Helaena!

159
00:17:43.041 --> 00:17:47.796
A curse. a curse on
Rhaenyra. the monstrous!

160
00:17:54.636 --> 00:17:58.181
It is yet unclear how the Keep
itself was breached.

161
00:17:58.556 --> 00:18:01.142
The boy's head
was severed from his body.

162
00:18:01.726 --> 00:18:04.145
Thousands witnessed the procession.

163
00:18:04.938 --> 00:18:08.316
And they are accusing me
of having a hand in this.

164
00:18:08.483 --> 00:18:09.776
It appears so.

165
00:18:10.026 --> 00:18:12.487
There have been messages
sent to that effect

166
00:18:12.821 --> 00:18:14.280
throughout the realm.

167
00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:19.160
We must send our own messages.
denying this vile allegation.

168
00:18:19.244 --> 00:18:20.870
I will do so at once

169
00:18:20.954 --> 00:18:23.248
but I'm not sure they will be
received in good faith.

170
00:18:23.331 --> 00:18:26.918
And we must double our guard.
here and in Driftmark.

171
00:18:27.752 --> 00:18:29.921
There will be swift retribution
in one form or another.

172
00:18:30.005 --> 00:18:31.756
I have seen to it. Your Grace.

173
00:18:33.216 --> 00:18:34.968
Let me fly out on Vermax.

174
00:18:35.260 --> 00:18:37.304
Rhaenys is needed in the Gullet
and I can watch for movements

175
00:18:37.387 --> 00:18:38.805
- from King's Landing.
- No.

176
00:18:40.974 --> 00:18:43.852
It must be said that the damage to
our position is immeasurable

177
00:18:44.144 --> 00:18:47.397
at a time when we most need
loyalty to our cause.

178
00:18:48.815 --> 00:18:50.150
But it's a lie.

179
00:18:51.610 --> 00:18:53.361
Having lost my own son

180
00:18:54.279 --> 00:18:58.366
that I would inflict such a thing
on Helaena. of all people.

181
00:18:59.826 --> 00:19:01.286
An innocent.

182
00:19:07.667 --> 00:19:12.672
The death of Prince Lucerys
was a shock and an insult.

183
00:19:13.131 --> 00:19:15.050
A mother so aggrieved might...

184
00:19:15.676 --> 00:19:17.886
naturally.
seek relief in retribution.

185
00:19:17.969 --> 00:19:19.513
Are you suggesting. Ser Alfred

186
00:19:19.596 --> 00:19:22.683
that my grief drove me to order
the decapitation of a child?

187
00:19:22.766 --> 00:19:26.728
I merely thought. perhaps.
an action taken in haste...

188
00:19:26.812 --> 00:19:28.230
Mind yourself.

189
00:19:47.249 --> 00:19:50.544
Did you send assassins
to murder children in their beds?

190
00:19:50.627 --> 00:19:52.296
I sent the queen's vengeance
for her son.

191
00:19:52.379 --> 00:19:54.006
What did you tell this "vengeance"?

192
00:19:54.089 --> 00:19:56.341
What did you say to him. Daemon

193
00:19:56.466 --> 00:19:58.343
that a boy lies dead
and I am accused of killing it?

194
00:19:58.427 --> 00:20:00.804
Mysaria provided me with names
and a subterfuge.

195
00:20:00.888 --> 00:20:02.639
I was clear in my instructions.

196
00:20:02.931 --> 00:20:05.768
Aemond. the brother of
Aegon the Usurper.

197
00:20:05.893 --> 00:20:06.935
I cannot be responsible
for a mistake.

198
00:20:07.019 --> 00:20:08.520
Cannot be responsible?

199
00:20:14.109 --> 00:20:18.197
If Aemond was not to be found.
what were your instructions then?

200
00:20:18.280 --> 00:20:19.740
They did not concern. in any way

201
00:20:19.823 --> 00:20:21.950
- that of a little child.
- You said that it was your aim

202
00:20:22.034 --> 00:20:23.369
to spill Hightower blood

203
00:20:23.452 --> 00:20:25.579
and if not Aemond.
then anyone would do.

204
00:20:25.662 --> 00:20:27.915
- No.
- You have wounded me.

205
00:20:27.998 --> 00:20:29.958
Weakened my claim to the throne

206
00:20:30.042 --> 00:20:34.088
my ability to raise an army.
my standing among my own council.

207
00:20:34.171 --> 00:20:36.507
I said no.

208
00:20:36.757 --> 00:20:38.175
I don't believe you.

209
00:20:49.562 --> 00:20:51.605
And so we come to it. at long last.

210
00:20:56.986 --> 00:20:58.404
Cannot trust you. Daemon.

211
00:21:00.948 --> 00:21:02.908
I've never trusted you. wholly

212
00:21:03.659 --> 00:21:06.162
much though I wished to.
willed myself to.

213
00:21:07.705 --> 00:21:10.332
But now I have seen that
your heart belongs only to you.

214
00:21:11.083 --> 00:21:13.919
And when I was a child.
I took this as a challenge.

215
00:21:14.003 --> 00:21:16.505
But I am older now.
I have challenges enough.

216
00:21:16.589 --> 00:21:18.591
- I have served you faithfully.
- Have you?

217
00:21:18.674 --> 00:21:21.302
Or have you used me as a tool

218
00:21:21.385 --> 00:21:24.263
with which to grasp
at your stolen inheritance?

219
00:21:42.615 --> 00:21:44.659
When Ser Erryk brought you the crown

220
00:21:45.326 --> 00:21:47.745
did I myself not place it
upon your brow?

221
00:21:47.828 --> 00:21:52.291
Yes. but before that.
you sought to lead a council of war

222
00:21:52.375 --> 00:21:55.169
while I labored alone
in my bedchamber.

223
00:21:55.252 --> 00:21:57.171
And afterward.
when I thought it meet to consider

224
00:21:57.255 --> 00:21:59.423
- the terms our foes put before us...
- A folly! A folly!

225
00:21:59.507 --> 00:22:01.634
To give up my brother's throne
to the traitorous lies

226
00:22:01.717 --> 00:22:05.221
- of Otto Hightower!
- My throne. Daemon. mine!

227
00:22:05.721 --> 00:22:08.182
I think you used
my words as an excuse

228
00:22:08.391 --> 00:22:10.017
to take your own revenge

229
00:22:11.018 --> 00:22:14.480
to indulge the darkness you keep
sheathed within you like a blade.

230
00:22:14.564 --> 00:22:15.898
You think me some kind of monster.

231
00:22:15.982 --> 00:22:17.024
I don't know what to think of you.

232
00:22:17.108 --> 00:22:19.569
I don't know what you are
or who it is you serve.

233
00:22:19.652 --> 00:22:22.405
Am I not on my way. even now.
to Harrenhal

234
00:22:22.488 --> 00:22:26.117
to raise an army
in your name. Rhaenyra? Yours!

235
00:22:34.292 --> 00:22:38.671
Do you accept me
as your queen and ruler?

236
00:22:41.799 --> 00:22:44.552
Or do you cling. even now.
to what you think you lost?

237
00:22:47.513 --> 00:22:49.140
What I think I lost?

238
00:22:49.432 --> 00:22:51.309
You did not lose it. You gave it away

239
00:22:52.185 --> 00:22:55.438
because you thought ever and only
of your own glory

240
00:22:55.521 --> 00:22:57.106
and not of my father in his grief

241
00:22:57.190 --> 00:22:58.316
- who needed you.
- Your father was a coward

242
00:22:58.399 --> 00:23:01.361
who knew I was the stronger son.
that I was the leader of men

243
00:23:01.444 --> 00:23:02.987
and he was afraid
to be seen in my shadow.

244
00:23:03.071 --> 00:23:04.405
Is that what you understand
of your own brother?

245
00:23:04.489 --> 00:23:07.325
You know him better than I do.
who was raised at his side?

246
00:23:07.408 --> 00:23:10.203
Do you believe he made you heir
because of your great wisdom?

247
00:23:10.328 --> 00:23:11.829
Because of your virtue?

248
00:23:12.497 --> 00:23:14.999
- How dare you.
- Or did he merely use you as a tool

249
00:23:15.083 --> 00:23:18.336
to put me in my place
because he was afraid of me?

250
00:23:18.419 --> 00:23:19.462
Because he knew your legacy

251
00:23:19.546 --> 00:23:21.172
unlike mine.
would never outshine his own.

252
00:23:21.256 --> 00:23:24.509
He was not afraid of you. Daemon!

253
00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:30.181
He could not trust you
any more than I can trust you.

254
00:23:30.265 --> 00:23:33.309
He was a fool who sought greatness

255
00:23:33.393 --> 00:23:35.145
but shrank from spilling blood
to achieve it.

256
00:23:35.228 --> 00:23:37.272
And I see you
will suffer the same fate.

257
00:23:38.565 --> 00:23:40.608
You struck down a child.

258
00:23:44.529 --> 00:23:46.197
It was a mistake.

259
00:23:51.035 --> 00:23:52.412
You're pathetic.

260
00:24:28.323 --> 00:24:29.616
Father?

261
00:24:38.917 --> 00:24:40.669
You wish to see me. Your Grace?

262
00:24:50.220 --> 00:24:51.805
When morning comes

263
00:24:51.930 --> 00:24:55.475
take Moondancer and
keep a watch on King's Landing.

264
00:24:56.184 --> 00:24:58.103
I must know which course
they take next.

265
00:24:58.603 --> 00:24:59.938
I will be vigilant.

266
00:25:00.856 --> 00:25:02.441
I depend on you. Baela.

267
00:25:03.567 --> 00:25:05.861
Stay high and keep your distance.

268
00:25:07.195 --> 00:25:09.072
We can afford no further mistakes.

269
00:25:19.374 --> 00:25:20.751
My father?

270
00:25:25.005 --> 00:25:26.757
He must follow his own path.

271
00:27:19.745 --> 00:27:21.038
If you please. m'lord.

272
00:28:45.873 --> 00:28:47.208
Have you told anyone?

273
00:28:51.045 --> 00:28:52.672
What do you take me for?

274
00:28:54.841 --> 00:28:56.592
One who seeks absolution.

275
00:28:57.927 --> 00:28:59.762
There is none for what I've done.

276
00:30:37.235 --> 00:30:38.528
What is this?

277
00:30:42.157 --> 00:30:44.409
It's a reminder of yesterday.
I think.

278
00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:46.244
The procession was muddy.

279
00:30:46.328 --> 00:30:48.747
- I'll replace it hence.
- Do it now.

280
00:30:51.833 --> 00:30:53.335
The night was long. Ser Criston

281
00:30:53.627 --> 00:30:56.880
- and I had not eaten...
- You defy my authority. Ser Arryk.

282
00:30:59.007 --> 00:31:00.300
I do not.

283
00:31:00.509 --> 00:31:04.888
The white cloak is a symbol
of our purity. our fidelity.

284
00:31:05.847 --> 00:31:07.682
Kingsguard are a sacred trust.

285
00:31:08.183 --> 00:31:11.311
Will you so easily sully
our ancient honor?

286
00:31:25.325 --> 00:31:26.994
I have erred. my lord.

287
00:31:28.453 --> 00:31:29.830
I'll remedy the error.

288
00:31:35.377 --> 00:31:37.254
Where were you
when Jaehaerys was murdered?

289
00:31:42.175 --> 00:31:43.468
With King Aegon.

290
00:31:45.012 --> 00:31:46.513
And you were not
in the private quarters

291
00:31:46.597 --> 00:31:48.432
where you might have
prevented the crime.

292
00:31:48.765 --> 00:31:52.060
His Grace wished to entertain
his companions in the throne room.

293
00:31:52.352 --> 00:31:53.687
But if you had thought
to go upstairs...

294
00:31:53.770 --> 00:31:55.481
Where were you. Lord Commander?

295
00:31:57.149 --> 00:31:59.568
And why has Helaena the Queen
been granted no sworn protector?

296
00:31:59.651 --> 00:32:00.819
Surely once she ascended. she...

297
00:32:00.903 --> 00:32:03.864
Your brother is a thief
and a traitor to the crown.

298
00:32:13.082 --> 00:32:14.541
You well know how it pains me.

299
00:32:14.625 --> 00:32:16.585
How are we to know that
you do not secretly share

300
00:32:16.668 --> 00:32:19.004
- his sentiments?
- I denounced him before the king.

301
00:32:19.421 --> 00:32:21.632
We were one soul in two bodies. yes.

302
00:32:22.341 --> 00:32:24.968
If I'd shared his sentiments.
I would've fled with him.

303
00:32:26.887 --> 00:32:29.014
First. your brother betrays us.

304
00:32:32.017 --> 00:32:33.644
And then the young prince

305
00:32:35.062 --> 00:32:38.399
is murdered on your watch.

306
00:32:38.482 --> 00:32:39.775
You are mad. Ser.

307
00:32:40.359 --> 00:32:41.610
Mad!
You cannot think that I did this!

308
00:32:41.694 --> 00:32:43.696
What I think has no relevance!

309
00:32:47.241 --> 00:32:49.451
You have brought disgrace
upon our ranks...

310
00:32:53.289 --> 00:32:55.207
and now you must restore it.

311
00:32:57.334 --> 00:32:58.627
How am I to do that?

312
00:33:15.478 --> 00:33:16.771
You will go to Dragonstone

313
00:33:16.854 --> 00:33:19.482
and strike down Rhaenyra
in her own halls.

314
00:33:21.484 --> 00:33:23.402
The way she sought to do with Aemond.

315
00:33:24.153 --> 00:33:26.822
We will pay the princess back
in her own bloody coin.

316
00:33:28.949 --> 00:33:29.992
Alone?

317
00:33:30.076 --> 00:33:31.994
Does your courage fail you.
Ser Arryk?

318
00:33:32.078 --> 00:33:33.454
It's not a matter of courage.

319
00:33:33.996 --> 00:33:36.916
The castle is defended
against all enemies. now especially.

320
00:33:38.626 --> 00:33:40.628
- How would I enter?
- Your twin serves there

321
00:33:40.711 --> 00:33:42.004
at the pleasure
of the so-called queen.

322
00:33:42.088 --> 00:33:44.131
They will mistake you for him
if you play the part.

323
00:33:45.383 --> 00:33:49.303
We are sworn to serve forthrightly.
not to traffic in deception.

324
00:33:49.387 --> 00:33:50.888
Put down the pretender

325
00:33:50.972 --> 00:33:53.766
and you will end a war
before it begins.

326
00:34:01.816 --> 00:34:03.568
- If they see the two of us...
- You must not let that happen.

327
00:34:03.651 --> 00:34:06.279
- You would send me to my death.
- Or to triumph.

328
00:34:09.073 --> 00:34:10.533
And glory.

329
00:34:16.414 --> 00:34:17.915
Now. will you go?

330
00:34:19.459 --> 00:34:22.295
Or must I question
your loyalty to the king?

331
00:34:28.134 --> 00:34:31.512
As you command. my lord.

332
00:34:41.564 --> 00:34:42.982
You missed supper.

333
00:34:43.941 --> 00:34:45.318
I wasn't hungry.

334
00:34:45.735 --> 00:34:47.487
I don't think anyone was. really.

335
00:34:48.613 --> 00:34:50.156
Too many empty seats.

336
00:34:51.991 --> 00:34:53.284
Do you know where he went?

337
00:34:54.243 --> 00:34:56.037
Harrenhal. I would think.

338
00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:02.126
Sometimes I think I hate him.

339
00:35:06.172 --> 00:35:08.967
It's hard. with fathers.

340
00:35:10.218 --> 00:35:12.053
What do you remember of my uncle?

341
00:35:13.304 --> 00:35:14.931
He taught us to catch fish

342
00:35:16.808 --> 00:35:19.602
and sing sailors' shanties.

343
00:35:20.270 --> 00:35:21.938
He had a weakness for cake.

344
00:35:24.190 --> 00:35:27.861
And Ser Harwin Strong?

345
00:35:30.029 --> 00:35:33.116
He was gentle. and fierce.

346
00:35:36.161 --> 00:35:39.372
They called him "Breakbones."

347
00:35:41.916 --> 00:35:44.586
He loved us. I think.

348
00:35:46.254 --> 00:35:47.547
Of course. he did.

349
00:35:53.595 --> 00:35:54.888
I miss Luke.

350
00:36:36.429 --> 00:36:38.306
Daemon sent them to kill me.

351
00:36:41.017 --> 00:36:42.310
I was out.

352
00:36:43.603 --> 00:36:44.896
You were with me.

353
00:36:45.814 --> 00:36:47.441
In truth. I am proud

354
00:36:48.775 --> 00:36:50.902
that he considers me such a foe.

355
00:36:53.071 --> 00:36:55.741
And that he seeks
to murder me in my bed.

356
00:36:56.616 --> 00:36:58.076
He's afraid of me.

357
00:36:59.244 --> 00:37:00.871
As well he should be.

358
00:37:02.456 --> 00:37:05.125
The boy is grown into a man.

359
00:37:05.375 --> 00:37:07.210
No. Not here.

360
00:37:17.846 --> 00:37:20.182
I do regret that business with Luke.

361
00:37:21.308 --> 00:37:23.268
I lost my temper that day.

362
00:37:23.477 --> 00:37:25.312
I am sorry for it.

363
00:37:25.854 --> 00:37:27.564
I am glad to hear it.

364
00:37:30.692 --> 00:37:33.111
They used to tease me. you know?

365
00:37:35.739 --> 00:37:37.199
Because I was different.

366
00:37:40.327 --> 00:37:43.997
I would remind you only that
when princes lose their temper

367
00:37:44.248 --> 00:37:46.291
it is often others who suffer.

368
00:37:49.920 --> 00:37:51.547
The smallfolk.

369
00:37:52.506 --> 00:37:53.549
Like me.

370
00:37:58.220 --> 00:37:59.513
How is she?

371
00:38:00.472 --> 00:38:01.765
Much the same.

372
00:38:13.944 --> 00:38:16.321
The markets have been running low
since the blockade.

373
00:38:17.239 --> 00:38:19.616
Surely the city cannot yet be
short of food.

374
00:38:20.409 --> 00:38:22.995
I think not. but people are afraid.

375
00:38:23.495 --> 00:38:25.914
Those with means are hoarding
everything they can.

376
00:38:28.709 --> 00:38:31.420
I walked two hours today
to find a chicken for the pot

377
00:38:32.087 --> 00:38:34.173
and paid three times
as much as I should have.

378
00:38:48.896 --> 00:38:50.606
The selfishness of people.

379
00:38:51.523 --> 00:38:55.236
I cannot blame anyone for doing
what I myself would do if I could.

380
00:38:55.319 --> 00:38:56.862
I don't think
you'd let children go hungry

381
00:38:56.946 --> 00:38:58.489
while you filled your own cellars.

382
00:38:59.365 --> 00:39:01.367
Lucky we don't have
enough coin to find out.

383
00:39:03.869 --> 00:39:06.497
The king has promised us some relief.

384
00:39:08.499 --> 00:39:09.792
Did he say when?

385
00:39:16.924 --> 00:39:18.342
I'm afraid. Hugh.

386
00:39:28.644 --> 00:39:32.189
I see all your great adventures
have done nothing for your looks.

387
00:39:36.027 --> 00:39:38.988
Well met. brother.
after many months away.

388
00:39:48.998 --> 00:39:50.333
I missed you.

389
00:39:52.376 --> 00:39:53.711
Did you slay many pirates?

390
00:39:53.794 --> 00:39:55.671
Oh. more than you. to be sure.

391
00:39:55.922 --> 00:39:56.964
A jest.

392
00:39:57.048 --> 00:39:59.592
One you may regret
as you're supping alone tonight.

393
00:40:00.176 --> 00:40:01.552
I regret it already.

394
00:40:02.094 --> 00:40:04.138
I've broken my teeth on hard tack.
Addam.

395
00:40:04.222 --> 00:40:07.683
Say you have a pot of your goat stew
simmering at home.

396
00:40:07.892 --> 00:40:09.185
You're in luck.

397
00:40:10.061 --> 00:40:11.729
In more ways than one.

398
00:40:12.480 --> 00:40:14.273
I hear Lord Corlys himself

399
00:40:14.357 --> 00:40:16.442
commended you
for your service to him.

400
00:40:18.903 --> 00:40:21.030
- He did.
- Will you sail with him

401
00:40:21.280 --> 00:40:22.865
when his ship has been repaired?

402
00:40:23.991 --> 00:40:26.536
I am one of a dozen shipwrights
now called from Hull

403
00:40:26.619 --> 00:40:28.579
to attend with all speed
to your fleet.

404
00:40:29.622 --> 00:40:30.957
He made no offer.

405
00:40:32.458 --> 00:40:34.502
And I would rather he didn't.
truth be told.

406
00:40:34.585 --> 00:40:36.421
Do not be foolish. Alyn.

407
00:40:38.339 --> 00:40:41.300
To serve with the Sea Snake
is to make your fortune.

408
00:40:41.384 --> 00:40:43.594
Had I such a chance.
I would leap at it.

409
00:40:43.678 --> 00:40:45.930
That's because you haven't seen
what I've seen.

410
00:40:46.264 --> 00:40:48.641
There is a war brewing. Addam.

411
00:40:48.725 --> 00:40:49.767
A real one.

412
00:40:49.851 --> 00:40:52.520
Another opportunity
to distinguish yourself.

413
00:40:52.603 --> 00:40:55.148
- Remind him of your worth.
- I need no favors.

414
00:40:55.231 --> 00:40:58.359
But brother. he owes you. he owes us.

415
00:41:00.403 --> 00:41:01.988
Does the stew have carrots in it?

416
00:41:07.744 --> 00:41:09.412
I mistrust this silence.

417
00:41:11.205 --> 00:41:14.083
Daemon flies when we most need
his hand at the oar.

418
00:41:15.877 --> 00:41:18.588
Devotion has never sat well with him.

419
00:41:18.880 --> 00:41:22.926
Where he goes.
he wishes to be his own master.

420
00:41:25.595 --> 00:41:27.138
He is the king consort.

421
00:41:30.767 --> 00:41:33.269
But he is not the king.

422
00:41:33.812 --> 00:41:36.523
Neither am I. but I manage.

423
00:41:39.651 --> 00:41:42.028
I too have felt
the crown pass over me.

424
00:41:42.112 --> 00:41:44.322
It is a hard thing to accept.

425
00:41:47.117 --> 00:41:50.245
And now Viserys is dead
and all claims are in doubt.

426
00:41:51.538 --> 00:41:54.874
You do not think
Daemon will challenge her?

427
00:41:57.043 --> 00:41:58.461
Not as such.

428
00:42:02.716 --> 00:42:05.176
But neither can he allow her
to command him.

429
00:42:05.719 --> 00:42:07.012
Pity.

430
00:42:07.804 --> 00:42:11.891
I have. on occasion.
found that to be quite enjoyable.

431
00:42:16.896 --> 00:42:18.773
Let us take him at his word.

432
00:42:20.358 --> 00:42:23.486
If he can take Harrenhal.
all may well be forgiven.

433
00:42:24.321 --> 00:42:26.364
In the meantime. I am here.

434
00:42:28.283 --> 00:42:29.576
And Meleys.

435
00:42:33.038 --> 00:42:35.290
We will not let the queen falter.

436
00:43:04.569 --> 00:43:07.072
The lady Mysaria. Your Grace.

437
00:43:18.375 --> 00:43:21.003
You're aware of yesterday's events
in King's Landing?

438
00:43:23.088 --> 00:43:24.381
I am.

439
00:43:25.215 --> 00:43:27.301
Tell me what part you played
in their unfolding.

440
00:43:27.384 --> 00:43:28.969
I had nothing to do with it.

441
00:43:29.052 --> 00:43:31.513
I know you are entwined
with the usurpers

442
00:43:31.638 --> 00:43:33.974
that you aided them
in denying me my birthright.

443
00:43:34.057 --> 00:43:36.268
I took profits from an inevitability.

444
00:43:36.560 --> 00:43:38.520
I regret it now.

445
00:43:38.729 --> 00:43:40.022
I'm sure you do.

446
00:43:43.066 --> 00:43:44.359
Who are you?

447
00:43:45.903 --> 00:43:47.279
A prisoner.

448
00:43:59.416 --> 00:44:02.961
I gave Daemon two names.
That is the extent of it.

449
00:44:03.045 --> 00:44:05.589
And I did not wish to do that much.

450
00:44:06.381 --> 00:44:08.425
He said it was
the price of my freedom.

451
00:44:17.226 --> 00:44:18.977
Does he say otherwise?

452
00:44:19.812 --> 00:44:21.105
He is gone.

453
00:44:23.107 --> 00:44:24.483
For how long?

454
00:44:25.693 --> 00:44:28.779
A week. or forever. I do not know.

455
00:44:34.285 --> 00:44:38.122
He does do that. doesn't he?

456
00:44:47.298 --> 00:44:48.966
You remember me now.

457
00:44:53.137 --> 00:44:54.638
He said he would marry you.

458
00:44:57.224 --> 00:45:01.187
- He said you carried his child.
- Not everyone found the jest funny.

459
00:45:01.604 --> 00:45:06.692
And now it seems he's done it again.
made a promise and then slipped away.

460
00:45:06.775 --> 00:45:09.195
You trade in the secrets
of the Red Keep.

461
00:45:10.029 --> 00:45:12.907
Your web runs unseen
through King's Landing.

462
00:45:12.990 --> 00:45:16.619
And now. when my enemy coils
himself to strike at me...

463
00:45:16.702 --> 00:45:21.373
I can do nothing now but ask you
to honor your husband's words.

464
00:45:21.749 --> 00:45:23.751
It would not serve me
to set you free.

465
00:45:26.504 --> 00:45:30.132
At best. I lose an asset to my cause.

466
00:45:32.426 --> 00:45:34.345
At worst.
you betray me in some foul way.

467
00:45:34.428 --> 00:45:37.306
I have no interest in betraying you.
Your Grace.

468
00:45:39.517 --> 00:45:40.810
So you say.

469
00:45:49.860 --> 00:45:52.238
I was brought to Westeros
with nothing.

470
00:45:52.572 --> 00:45:55.324
I toiled in service. I stole.

471
00:45:55.408 --> 00:45:58.077
I sold my own body for coin or bread.

472
00:45:58.494 --> 00:46:00.746
And I listened.

473
00:46:00.997 --> 00:46:02.707
I collected confidences.

474
00:46:02.790 --> 00:46:05.251
I made myself valuable
to powerful men.

475
00:46:05.334 --> 00:46:07.461
Bit by bit. I earned my living.

476
00:46:07.545 --> 00:46:10.756
A house. a household. a home.

477
00:46:11.716 --> 00:46:13.509
Then they set it all aflame.

478
00:46:15.094 --> 00:46:18.806
- Who did?
- The Hightowers. I can only assume.

479
00:46:19.932 --> 00:46:24.729
The Hand did not like it
when I showed my teeth.

480
00:46:26.397 --> 00:46:28.065
But I thank him for it.

481
00:46:28.775 --> 00:46:34.072
For too long. I made it my aim
to be of consequence.

482
00:46:34.238 --> 00:46:38.493
But now. I see that was
the wish of a child.

483
00:46:39.160 --> 00:46:43.039
Daemon. Otto Hightower.

484
00:46:43.456 --> 00:46:44.957
Makes no difference.

485
00:46:45.249 --> 00:46:47.752
They will never accept me.

486
00:46:48.169 --> 00:46:50.380
I might as well
have remained a whore.

487
00:46:56.970 --> 00:46:58.554
How did you get that scar?

488
00:48:38.405 --> 00:48:39.698
Oh no.

489
00:48:40.574 --> 00:48:41.867
My son.

490
00:48:58.425 --> 00:49:01.344
- Who are they?
- Ratcatchers.

491
00:49:02.596 --> 00:49:04.222
In the king's employ.

492
00:49:06.391 --> 00:49:07.809
What'd they do?

493
00:49:35.587 --> 00:49:36.922
What have you done?

494
00:49:41.802 --> 00:49:43.679
The ratcatchers!

495
00:49:46.390 --> 00:49:47.808
I had them hanged.

496
00:49:50.602 --> 00:49:53.689
The maggot who took my son
confessed to an accomplice.

497
00:49:54.648 --> 00:49:57.067
He could not say for certain
which man it was. so.

498
00:49:57.151 --> 00:49:58.777
- Idiot!
- Beware how you speak

499
00:49:58.861 --> 00:50:00.195
to your king. my lord.

500
00:50:00.279 --> 00:50:04.533
The king is my grandson
and my grandson is a fool!

501
00:50:04.616 --> 00:50:08.162
He's worse than a fool!
He's murdered innocent men!

502
00:50:08.287 --> 00:50:09.329
And one guilty one.

503
00:50:09.413 --> 00:50:12.624
And hanged them from the walls
of the city for all to see!

504
00:50:12.708 --> 00:50:14.835
Plot against the king. and I will
pay it back a hundred times...

505
00:50:14.918 --> 00:50:17.671
They are fathers
and brothers and sons!

506
00:50:18.297 --> 00:50:21.842
And their wives and children
gather now at our gates to weep

507
00:50:21.925 --> 00:50:23.802
and curse your name!

508
00:50:35.439 --> 00:50:39.526
With your child's blood.
we bought their approval.

509
00:50:39.610 --> 00:50:42.821
With your mother's tears.
we made a bitter sacrifice

510
00:50:42.905 --> 00:50:44.907
against the deprivations to come.

511
00:50:44.990 --> 00:50:46.992
And you've thrown it away.

512
00:50:48.452 --> 00:50:49.912
After all I've done for you.

513
00:50:49.995 --> 00:50:53.415
Thoughtless. feckless...

514
00:50:54.875 --> 00:50:56.001
self-indulgent.

515
00:50:56.085 --> 00:50:57.795
At least I did something.

516
00:50:57.962 --> 00:51:00.965
I have not answered injury
to the crown with. what?

517
00:51:01.048 --> 00:51:04.385
Wailing and currying favor
with the fishwives?

518
00:51:04.468 --> 00:51:06.095
I will not be thought weak.

519
00:51:06.178 --> 00:51:08.889
Even now. news of Rhaenyra's
monstrous crime

520
00:51:08.973 --> 00:51:10.015
spreads through the realm.

521
00:51:10.099 --> 00:51:13.561
The great houses falter.
They cannot but come to our side.

522
00:51:13.644 --> 00:51:16.147
I wish to spill blood. not ink!

523
00:51:17.064 --> 00:51:18.357
We must act.

524
00:51:19.525 --> 00:51:21.402
Ser Criston Cole has acted.

525
00:51:30.578 --> 00:51:36.250
And what has Ser Criston Cole done?

526
00:51:38.085 --> 00:51:40.254
He has sent Ser Arryk
to slay Rhaenyra.

527
00:51:45.801 --> 00:51:47.094
Alone?

528
00:51:49.555 --> 00:51:51.974
He's pretending to be his own twin.
Brilliant.

529
00:51:56.771 --> 00:51:58.397
Gods help us all.

530
00:51:59.273 --> 00:52:01.442
It's time the bitch queen
paid a price.

531
00:52:05.154 --> 00:52:08.908
And you acceded to this prank

532
00:52:08.991 --> 00:52:11.869
without consulting me or the council?

533
00:52:12.537 --> 00:52:15.665
Instead of judgment.
you display impetuousness

534
00:52:15.748 --> 00:52:18.668
and diminish us in the eyes
of our enemy!

535
00:52:18.751 --> 00:52:21.337
Ill-considered. trifling!

536
00:52:32.098 --> 00:52:35.476
Do you never think of
your father? His...

537
00:52:36.978 --> 00:52:38.938
forbearance. his...

538
00:52:39.689 --> 00:52:41.774
judiciousness. his...

539
00:52:45.111 --> 00:52:47.238
his dignity.

540
00:52:47.322 --> 00:52:49.073
Fuck dignity!

541
00:52:49.824 --> 00:52:51.242
I want revenge.

542
00:52:53.911 --> 00:52:55.580
My father is dead.

543
00:52:58.249 --> 00:52:59.584
He is.

544
00:53:01.544 --> 00:53:03.922
And we are the poorer for it.

545
00:53:19.312 --> 00:53:21.231
He was right about you.

546
00:53:24.108 --> 00:53:25.527
He made me king.

547
00:53:30.657 --> 00:53:32.534
Is that what you think?

548
00:53:39.290 --> 00:53:41.960
Remove your badge. Ser Otto.

549
00:53:50.051 --> 00:53:51.886
You were my father's Hand.

550
00:53:53.596 --> 00:53:54.889
Not mine.

551
00:53:55.974 --> 00:53:57.267
Take it off.

552
00:53:59.644 --> 00:54:01.187
You wouldn't dare.

553
00:54:04.399 --> 00:54:05.859
I have dared

554
00:54:06.943 --> 00:54:08.987
and I find it stimulating.

555
00:54:19.122 --> 00:54:21.082
Insolent pup.

556
00:54:25.253 --> 00:54:26.796
You think yourself clever

557
00:54:26.880 --> 00:54:30.008
but without a strong Hand
at your side...

558
00:54:33.386 --> 00:54:34.679
to guide?

559
00:54:38.308 --> 00:54:39.643
Give it to Cole.

560
00:54:44.397 --> 00:54:45.690
Your Grace?

561
00:54:50.112 --> 00:54:53.323
In this hour. you have proven
yourself of more worth

562
00:54:53.407 --> 00:54:55.283
than a hundred old men.

563
00:54:59.079 --> 00:55:03.083
My new Hand will be a steel fist.

564
00:55:04.209 --> 00:55:08.672
You will regret this.

565
00:55:10.382 --> 00:55:11.758
Give it to him.

566
00:55:29.860 --> 00:55:31.320
You are dismissed.

567
00:55:42.581 --> 00:55:44.249
I do not know if I trust you.

568
00:55:45.000 --> 00:55:48.212
And I sense that
there is danger in you yet.

569
00:55:50.380 --> 00:55:53.383
But I will keep the word of my house
if you say that it was given.

570
00:56:01.683 --> 00:56:02.976
You may go.

571
00:56:04.186 --> 00:56:05.479
Your Grace.

572
00:56:05.562 --> 00:56:09.024
There's a Velaryon ship in the harbor
bound for Myr by way of Pentos.

573
00:56:09.233 --> 00:56:10.859
I will see that
you are given passage.

574
00:56:11.819 --> 00:56:14.196
I'm not so unworldly as to
let you fly free.

575
00:56:14.279 --> 00:56:17.366
I am... Thank you.

576
00:56:20.536 --> 00:56:22.621
Ser Erryk.
Mysaria will be leaving us.

577
00:56:22.746 --> 00:56:24.456
Let her collect her things.

578
00:56:24.540 --> 00:56:27.501
Then have someone take her down
and secure her berth on the <i>Corwyn.</i>

579
00:56:27.876 --> 00:56:29.211
Your Grace.

580
00:57:15.091 --> 00:57:16.384
A moment.

581
00:57:46.122 --> 00:57:47.415
Ser Erryk.

582
00:57:48.833 --> 00:57:51.752
- I thought you were within.
- A sorry lack of vigilance.

583
00:57:52.712 --> 00:57:54.589
The enemy is about. good ser.

584
00:59:55.877 --> 00:59:57.963
Please try and lay down. Your Grace.

585
00:59:58.463 --> 00:59:59.839
Thank you. Elinda.

586
01:00:24.030 --> 01:00:25.323
Ser Erryk.

587
01:00:27.576 --> 01:00:28.910
It's been a strange day.

588
01:00:30.203 --> 01:00:33.165
I'm restless.
I will stand this evening's duty.

589
01:00:46.970 --> 01:00:49.306
You must sleep tonight. Your Grace.

590
01:00:49.514 --> 01:00:51.391
Let me ask the maester for a draught.

591
01:00:52.017 --> 01:00:53.602
Perhaps that would be best.

592
01:00:55.687 --> 01:00:56.980
Thank you. Elinda.

593
01:01:08.283 --> 01:01:09.576
Ser Erryk?

594
01:01:17.417 --> 01:01:20.879
Believe me. I had no choice.

595
01:01:21.088 --> 01:01:22.422
I don't understand.

596
01:01:22.631 --> 01:01:24.007
Brother!

597
01:01:26.635 --> 01:01:28.011
Do not do this.

598
01:01:28.845 --> 01:01:30.138
I beg you.

599
01:01:32.349 --> 01:01:34.268
You were the one
who betrayed us. Erryk.

600
01:01:56.623 --> 01:01:59.126
Run. Elinda! Run and find Ser Lorent!

601
01:02:37.331 --> 01:02:39.500
- Your Grace!
- Ser Lorent!

602
01:02:45.673 --> 01:02:47.007
With me. Your Grace!

603
01:02:52.930 --> 01:02:54.306
Which? Which is Erryk?

604
01:03:05.109 --> 01:03:08.446
- We were born together.
- You parted us!

605
01:03:10.448 --> 01:03:12.324
But I still love you. Brother.

606
01:04:05.711 --> 01:04:07.004
Your Grace.

607
01:04:10.508 --> 01:04:11.801
Erryk.

608
01:04:12.718 --> 01:04:14.053
Forgive me.

609
01:04:15.179 --> 01:04:16.472
No!

610
01:04:16.556 --> 01:04:17.849
No!

611
01:04:27.233 --> 01:04:30.528
It is ignorance and vanity.

612
01:04:32.488 --> 01:04:35.950
You know as well as I do
that Aegon must be kept in check.

613
01:04:36.034 --> 01:04:38.786
As does Ser Criston.
The two of them together.

614
01:04:40.330 --> 01:04:41.873
Ser Criston is not temperate

615
01:04:43.249 --> 01:04:44.834
but his devotion
cannot be questioned.

616
01:04:44.917 --> 01:04:47.211
- If it does come to war...
- He's ensured it.

617
01:04:48.338 --> 01:04:52.383
He's young and unschooled.
His faith is in steel and bone.

618
01:04:52.467 --> 01:04:54.260
He has not the long view.

619
01:04:54.677 --> 01:04:55.970
None of them do.

620
01:04:56.763 --> 01:04:58.556
They wish now
not for the good of the realm

621
01:04:58.640 --> 01:05:02.352
but for the petty satisfaction
of vengeance.

622
01:05:06.022 --> 01:05:07.440
Aegon is still malleable.

623
01:05:08.691 --> 01:05:11.027
It is the death of the child
that has unstrung him.

624
01:05:18.034 --> 01:05:19.744
I can't stay here.

625
01:05:22.038 --> 01:05:23.915
Exiled from the council.

626
01:05:25.708 --> 01:05:27.794
Witness to the blundering
of our plans.

627
01:05:27.877 --> 01:05:29.712
I'll return to Oldtown.

628
01:05:31.631 --> 01:05:33.299
The Hightowers still have strength

629
01:05:33.383 --> 01:05:36.177
and you have a son there

630
01:05:36.469 --> 01:05:38.638
who will take
more kindly to instruction.

631
01:05:38.888 --> 01:05:41.683
Daeron may yet help us
in weeks to come.

632
01:05:46.646 --> 01:05:48.273
Go rather to Highgarden.

633
01:05:51.151 --> 01:05:54.612
The Tyrells must be taken in hand.
Their bannermen are wavering.

634
01:05:55.447 --> 01:05:57.282
While you're gone.
I'll speak sense to him.

635
01:05:57.866 --> 01:05:59.284
His blood will cool.

636
01:06:00.285 --> 01:06:01.911
In time. you may yet return.

637
01:06:15.467 --> 01:06:20.889
The young are peacocks.
all shrieking and feathers.

638
01:06:23.266 --> 01:06:25.060
But we will yet prevail

639
01:06:25.143 --> 01:06:27.604
and bring forth peace.
I still believe it.

640
01:06:29.397 --> 01:06:31.775
As long as you and I hold fast.

641
01:06:44.538 --> 01:06:45.831
I have sinned.

642
01:06:50.210 --> 01:06:52.462
I do not wish to hear of it.

